    In this exercise we are asked to reverse a string using Java. We can use StringBuilder or StringBuffer classes but here I am going to show you another way which uses just one loop and two variables. One variable holds the starting index of the string and other variable holds the ending index of the string. Then we swap the values between these indexes and move along by incrementing both indices by one unit till they meet somewhere in the middle.

    ##### Code Snippet:
    ```java
    import java.lang.*;
    import java.io.*;

    public class Solution{
      public static void main(String []args){
          /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT */
          String s= "GeeksforGeeks";
          int startIndex = 0;
          int endIndex = s.length() -1;

          while(startIndex<endIndex){
              char temp = s.charAt(startIndex);
              s = s.substring(0,startIndex)+s.charAt(endIndex)+s.substring(startIndex+1,endIndex)+temp+s.substring(endIndex+1);

              startIndex++;
              endIndex--;
          }
          System.out.println(s);
      }
    }```

