Write a function called `solution` which accepts one argument: A positive integer representing the amount of money in dollars. Return the minimum number of coins needed to make up that total change. Assume that there are infinite supply of all denominations of currency available. You may assume that there exists some solution. For example, if the dollar value passed into the function were 65, the returned answer would be 6 because we can use 2 quarters, 1 dime, and 1 nickel to represent $65.

Note that the coin values used here are not necessarily those found in U.S. currency! In fact, any set of unique positive integers will do.

#### Example
```javascript
