#### Problem Description:
    Given a number n, find the sum of all numbers between 1 and n which are divisible either by 3 or 7 but not both. For instance, when n=8 we get 1 + 3 + 6 = 10. When n=10 we get 1+2+3+4+6+7+8+10 = 36.

    #### Solution Overview:
    We can use two nested loops to iterate over the range [1..n] and calculate the required values inside them. In order to avoid calculating the same values twice, we need to keep track of those already calculated. To make sure we don’t miss any values due to overflow, we can maintain three separate variables – one for multiples of 3, one for multiples of 7 and another for multiples of 3 and 7. Finally, we add these three sums together to get our desired result.

